HEADWORD: Stot
<hw>Stot</hw> <pr>(st⟦ocr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>stotte</ets> a hack, jade, or worthless horse; cf. Sw.
<ets>stut</ets> a bull, Dan. <ets>stud</ets> an ox. Cf.
<er>Stoat</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A horse.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer. Thorold Rogers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A young bull or ox, especially one three years
old.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

